            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
                 PAGE: Welcome to nOS
            ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <div class="nos-page active" id="section-welcome">
                <div class="nos-welcome">

                    <!-- nav top -->
                    <nav class="nos-nav-bar nos-nav-bar--top" aria-label="Section navigation">
                        <span class="nos-nav-prev disabled">← Prev</span>
                        <a class="nos-nav-page" data-section="section-install">Installation and startup →</a>
                    </nav>

                    <!-- ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
                    <header class="nos-welcome-hero">
                        {# Logo SVG cubo + n — ripristinare quando pronto
                        <svg class="nos-logo-mark" viewBox="0 0 128 140" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="nOS logo">
                            <defs>
                                <linearGradient id="nos-logo-face-l" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
                                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#0f172a"/>
                                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0c1220"/>
                                </linearGradient>
                                <linearGradient id="nos-logo-face-r" x1="0%" y1="100%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
                                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#111c2e"/>
                                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0a1628"/>
                                </linearGradient>
                                <linearGradient id="nos-logo-face-t" x1="50%" y1="0%" x2="50%" y2="100%">
                                    <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#152238"/>
                                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0d1829"/>
                                </linearGradient>
                                <filter id="nos-logo-glow" x="-40%" y="-40%" width="180%" height="180%">
                                    <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="1.2" result="b"/>
                                    <feMerge>
                                        <feMergeNode in="b"/>
                                        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
                                    </feMerge>
                                </filter>
                            </defs>
                            <g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.85" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.95">
                                <path d="M 28 44 L 28 104 L 72 124 L 72 64 Z" fill="url(#nos-logo-face-l)"/>
                                <path d="M 72 64 L 116 40 L 116 100 L 72 124 Z" fill="url(#nos-logo-face-r)"/>
                                <path d="M 28 44 L 72 20 L 116 40 L 72 64 Z" fill="url(#nos-logo-face-t)"/>
                            </g>
                            <path d="M 72 64 L 72 124 M 72 64 L 116 40 M 72 64 L 28 44" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.85" opacity="0.42"/>
                            <g filter="url(#nos-logo-glow)">
                                <g transform="matrix(44, 20, 0, 60, 28, 44)">
                                    <g transform="translate(0.5, 0.5)">
                                        <text class="nos-n"
                                              x="-0.034"
                                              y="0.02"
                                              font-size="0.72"
                                              text-anchor="middle"
                                              dominant-baseline="central"
                                              fill="currentColor"
                                              opacity="0.94">n</text>
                                    </g>
                                </g>
                            </g>
                        </svg>
                        #}
                        <h1>Welcome to <span class="nos-n">n</span>OS</h1>
                        <p class="nos-welcome-tagline">
                            Build, test and deploy microservice applications<br>
                            for workflow automation and pipeline orchestration.
                        </p>
                    </header>

                    <!-- ── Lead paragraphs ───────────────────────────── -->
                    <div class="nos-welcome-leads">
                        <p class="nos-welcome-lead">
                            nOS is an open platform for building, running and monitoring modular automation
                            apps — from simple deterministic pipelines to advanced AI-driven workflows and
                            autonomous agents. Each unit of work is a <strong>node</strong>: independently
                            testable, reusable and observable. Nodes connect into <strong>workflows</strong>
                            that are triggered via multiple interfaces and monitored in real time.
                        </p>
                        <p class="nos-welcome-lead">
                            nOS is meant to sit in the organization like an <strong>intelligent gear</strong>
                            in the machinery of work: at the intersection of <strong>business processes</strong> and the
                            <strong>workforce</strong> that carries them out. It turns ad hoc scripts and one-off integrations
                            into a shared layer where deterministic steps, AI-assisted decisions and human handoffs meet the
                            same contracts, logs and interfaces — so teams can compose automation that respects how operations
                            actually run, and improve it incrementally without losing visibility or control.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <hr class="nos-divider">

                    <!-- ── Key Capabilities ──────────────────────────── -->
                    <section class="nos-welcome-section">
                        <p class="nos-section-title">Key Capabilities</p>
                        <div class="nos-features-grid">

                            <!-- 1 · Node Architecture -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="2"/><circle cx="12" cy="5" r="2"/><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="2"/><circle cx="12" cy="19" r="2"/><path d="M7 12h3m2 0h3M12 7v3m0 2v3"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Architecture</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>From Graphs to Agents</h3>
                                <p>Start with deterministic node graphs and progressively introduce AI nodes and orchestrator agents — all within the same framework and execution model.</p>
                                <div class="nos-chips">
                                    <span class="nos-chip">deterministic</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">AI nodes</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">agents</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 2 · Execution Interfaces -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 20V10M12 20V4M6 20v-6"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Interfaces</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Multiple Execution Interfaces</h3>
                                <p>Every node and workflow is immediately reachable via REST API, WebSocket, Webhook and MCP — no extra integration layer required.</p>
                                <div class="nos-badge-row">
                                    <span class="nos-badge"><span>REST</span>&nbsp;API</span>
                                    <span class="nos-badge"><span>WS</span>&nbsp;WebSocket</span>
                                    <span class="nos-badge"><span>↗</span>&nbsp;Webhook</span>
                                    <span class="nos-badge"><span>⬡</span>&nbsp;MCP</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 3 · Developer Console -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="4" width="20" height="16" rx="2"/><path d="M6 9l4 3-4 3M13 15h5"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Developer UI</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Interactive Developer Console</h3>
                                <p>A built-in console for running, inspecting and debugging nodes and workflows in real time — with structured output rendering, live event logs and an inline input form editor.</p>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 4 · End-User Apps -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><path d="M9 9h6M9 12h6M9 15h4"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">End-User Apps</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Dedicated User Interfaces</h3>
                                <p>Deploy purpose-built UIs for end users — standalone or embedded in existing products — for configuring parameters and consuming the outputs of automation apps.</p>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 5 · Identity & access control -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Security</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Authentication &amp; authorization</h3>
                                <p>Enterprise sign-in through <strong>SSO</strong> and supported identity providers, backed by authorization over <strong>users</strong>, <strong>groups</strong> and <strong>roles</strong>. Enforce who may access each automation app, API surface and dataset — keeping execution and data inside a controlled, auditable perimeter aligned with your security policies.</p>
                                <div class="nos-chips">
                                    <span class="nos-chip">SSO</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">IdPs</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">RBAC</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 6 · Observability -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Observability</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Complete Execution Logs</h3>
                                <p>Every request generates a structured, timestamped log stream — node events, state transitions, outputs and errors — accessible in real time or retrieved on demand.</p>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 7 · Execution Modes -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 7v5l3 3"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Execution</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Flexible Execution Modes</h3>
                                <p>Run workflows interactively in the console, trigger them in the background via API, or schedule recurring executions — all within the same runtime and observable through the same log model.</p>
                                <div class="nos-chips">
                                    <span class="nos-chip">interactive</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">background</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">scheduled</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Lifecycle hooks — nodes & custom workflows -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="2.5"/><circle cx="18" cy="6" r="2.5"/><circle cx="12" cy="18" r="2.5"/><path d="M8 7.5h8M12 8.5v7M13.5 17l3.5-8"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Extensibility</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Lifecycle hooks</h3>
                                <p>
                                    For <strong>custom nodes</strong> and <strong>advanced workflows</strong>, nOS exposes <strong>lifecycle hooks</strong>—override points around start, validation, execution, hand-offs, success and failure.
                                    Use them to enforce rules, <strong>gate or short-circuit</strong> a run, integrate external systems, and enrich <strong>event logs</strong> for traceability and debugging—without forking the engine: the same runtime, with finer <strong>flexibility</strong> and <strong>operational control</strong>.
                                </p>
                                <div class="nos-chips">
                                    <span class="nos-chip">nodes</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">workflows</span>
                                    <span class="nos-chip">control</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- 8 · Plugin Ecosystem — full width -->
                            <div class="nos-feature-card nos-feature-card--wide">
                                <div class="nos-feature-icon">
                                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L9.5 9.5 2 12l7.5 2.5L12 22l2.5-7.5L22 12l-7.5-2.5L12 2z"/><circle cx="19" cy="5" r="1.5"/><circle cx="5" cy="19" r="1"/></svg>
                                    <span class="nos-feature-label">Ecosystem</span>
                                </div>
                                <h3>Rich Plugin Ecosystem</h3>
                                <p>Extend nOS with a growing library of ready-to-use plugins — web scrapers, AI model integrations, data converters, storage connectors, notification services and more. Build your own nodes and workflows and share them with the ecosystem.</p>
                            </div>

                        </div>
                    </section>

